      "content": "i mean, i get the \"employee satisfaction\" part, but in a small town, if i have to raise prices just to cover the wage, my customers might just stop coming. it feels like the people proposing these hikes don't really understand how much harder it hits local shops compared to big corporations. do you think there's a way to see if these policies actually help the local economy or if they just end up hurting the small guys?",
